<div class="content"><h1>Cupp of Brotherhood</h1><p>The Cupp of Brotherhood award is given to one active member who, over the course of the academic year, most consistently displays the fraternity's Cardinal principle of Friendship.  This member continually fosters a spirit of brotherhood within the Chapter, and actively displays a genuine respect for other brothers in such a way that promotes the vision and mission of AFW-Epsilon. This award is given by a plurality chapter vote, and is awarded at Epsilon's annual formal.</p><p>The Cupp of Brotherhood is named after Epsilon alumnus Randall Cupp, who pledged in fall 1978.  Mr. Cupp, whose fraternity nickname is 'Admiral,' was the Chapter's first Distinguished Service Key recipient (1982), one of Epsilon's inaugural Gold Sash recipients, and is the founder of the Yellow Rose family flower.</p><p>Here is a list of Epsilon's Cupp of Brotherhood award recipients.</p>
<ul>
<li>2011 - Brendan O'Brien</li>
<li>2012 - Bryce Osman</li>
<li>2013 - Becky Delaware</li>
</ul>
